author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Dan Cook)
title: Cape volleyball rolls over Central 3-0
text:
Cape volleyball rolls over Central 3-0 Vikings move to 8-1 on season By Dan Cook | Oct 13, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook Cape senior captain Izzie Marsico taps over a kill in the Vikings' 3-0 win over the Knights. 
The Cape volleyball team keeps rolling along, moving to 8-1 on the season with a 25-14, 25-7, 25-18 win over the Golden Knights Oct. 8 at Sussex Central. 
Taylor Collier led the Lady Vikings with eight kills and four aces while Logan Shuttleworth assisted on 20 points. Izzie Marsico knocked down five kills, Kira Vitella made eight digs and Abby E'Nama had four kills. Maddy Holt and Alison Palmer each scored three kills. 
Payton Heck came off the bench to power in four aces while Mallory Jones made four assists. 
"I wasn't thrilled with our first set performance where we gave them half their points on our errors," said head coach Tyler Coupe. "In the second and third sets, we responded well." 
The whole team was a part of the victory for the Vikings. 
"I was happy to see both Payton Heck and Maddy Holt get into a rhythm behind the service line and for sophomore Mallory Jones to run offense the third set," Coupe said. 
"We lacked focus in the first set," said senior libero Kira Vitella. "We were really sloppy, but came together in the second and third sets to play the way we know how to play." 
Emily Truitt and Chrishlyn Wisniewski led the Golden Knights with seven kills and eight assists, respectively. Sussex Central moved to 2-6 on the season. 
The Vikings will host the Bucs of Milford Tuesday, Oct.13. Cape junior middle blocker Cailey Thornburg smashes a kill shot in the Vikings' clash over the Knights.
